HEADWORD: Yacca
<hw>Yac"ca</hw> <pr>(y⟦acr⟧k"k⟦adot⟧)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A West Indian name for two large timber trees
(<spn>Podocarpus coriaceus</spn>, and <spn>Podocarpus Purdicanus</spn>)
of the Yew family. The wood, which is much used, is pale brownish with
darker streaks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Yacht</ent>⟦br⟧
